We are LIVE in Bangkok, Thailand 🇹🇭 covering @dastreffenmag’s #DasTreffen7, the largest and most diverse Porsche gathering in the Asia Pacific region.

It’s been three years since I’ve been able to visit my brothers from Thailand, and it feels so good to be back. Few porsche communities are as crystallized as the Thai community, they move like one big family. 

This year represents 30 years of @porsche.thailand, incredible how far they have come since I first came to this event at their 25th anniversary in the country.

I am here with @nat_twiss covering all the cars and characters for the rest of today, keep an eye on @type7 for everything as it happens 💥👌
What is this, a @rwbthailand meet up for ants? 🐜🐜🐜🐜🐜

Awesome morning getting to know the @horizondriversclub and the Porsche community here in Singapore.

The most rewarding part of our job @type7 is getting to spend time with people that share our passion with communities around the world. Just like our friends in Thailand, SG Porsche enthusiasts overcome many barriers to ownership (crazy taxes, logistics). It only seems to crystallize these communities and make their shared enthusiasm that much more contagious, a remarkable thing when you consider that a car could have 300% tax 😳

The Rubystone 964RS for example is suspected to be the highest mileage RS in the world at 595,000KM on the clock, daily driven since delivered new here in Singapore. Allegedly the owner tried to order it without air conditioning because he wanted it to be a more pure driving experience, the importer talked him out of it. That said it’s probably one of the only in existence with a factory sunroof option…

More on that car and the rest of the crew here soon 🇸🇬

Exploring the ultimate Singaporean 🇸🇬 car cave @autoicons_official today, nothing goes better with an eclectic collection than a perfectly working FAEMA E61 Espresso machine ☕️

There are so many hidden gems and Easter eggs in @type7 Volume 4: @teamikuzawa edition, it’s a little difficult for me to choose where to start.

This is the first project ever published in house by @erg.media, and we used it as an excuse to try all of the printing techniques and materials that we have wanted to try for years.

The external shipping box was designed in collaboration with @houseindustries, while the cover and slipcase are interpretations of the DNA of @teamikuzawa’s Japanese racing heritage, designed by @thomaswalk. 

As we head to the launch of Type 7 Volume 4: Team Ikuzawa edition at @theofficialselfridges on April 26th I will be highlighting many of the details and surprises that come with every book.

This is the hardest that our team has ever worked on a print project before, and it’s only just the beginning.

Thanks to everyone for the support and investment in our Type 7 story since the very beginning. It’s been a serious honor for the @erg.media team to build this with and for all of you 🫶

During the production of @TYPE7 VOLUME 4: @TEAMIKUZAWA EDITION we set out with one solitary goal during our time in Japan: to tell the most complete visual and biographical story of Ikuzawa-san’s life and career possible.

Ikuzawa-san is no stranger to press, he’s been featured on the cover of magazines, broadcast on television, and canonized in Japanese media. But in our research nobody had ever quite scratched the surface in capturing just the depth of his story in the print medium.

To capture his story it meant that we needed to get to Japan, so @thomaswalk and I with the help of @porsche_japan were able to secure special entrance visas while the borders remained closed in the blisteringly hot summer of 2022.

Once inside Ikuzawa-san’s meticulous Atelier we assembled various photo studios to begin the laborious process of documenting his archive. @thomaswalk is a master of treating simple objects as works of art, and as we assembled a physical storyline it became clear that more and more pieces needed to be photographed for the 120 plus pages dedicated to Team Ikuzawa.

With every object comes a story, and we were lucky to be given unrestricted access to Ikuzawa-san and his daughter Mai. 

This represents the first time outside of his physical archive that people will be able to read the anecdotes of each object straight from the source, accompanied by first hand contextual storytelling from Ikuzawa and his family.

Type 7 Volume 4: Team Ikuzawa Edition drops exclusively @theofficialselfridges in store and online April 26th.

Found an old roll of film I hadn’t developed, always the best feeling 🎞️

This scene is 21 years old. I remember asking my friends as a 14 year old (only 3 years younger than ScarJo in this scene) what a midlife crisis was. 

The etymology of the joke is rooted in a deeply 1990s mentality, where certain things were only unlocked after certain boxes were checked. You didn’t get to drive the Porsche until you hit Management level. 

My Dad grew up restoring wrecked Porsches with his Dad. When he bought our 1976 911S he paid around $5k USD. 30+ years after he took ownership that car is still on the road in better condition than when he bought it. It’s moved all around the world, been rebuilt, crashed, rebuilt again, loved, enjoyed and adored.

I love that today I can name dozens of close friends who are younger than me who drive Porsche, transaxle and rear-engine alike. I love that this joke no longer really fits in today’s automotive landscape. I love seeing how far we have come since this movie that I love was released.

Cc: @type7

Our two babies on display and for sale @daikanyama.tsutaya in the @daikanyama.cars selection, truly one of the most magical book stores in the world.

When we began publishing the @type7 books at @erg.media it was always our high water mark that they had to be good enough to be sold in this particular bookstore. It is the Super Bowl of niche bookstores for us. We are now celebrating our 3rd year as a featured publisher at T-Site.

It’s been a long road, but it’s only just the beginning. Thank you to everyone who has been a part of turning these dreams into reality.

Tomorrow at 18:30 I will be on site for 1 hour to meet any former and future collectors of our books, and if they would like I’m happy to sign them as a symbol of our team’s gratitude.

🏆 Perfect Saturday in Tokyo 🏆

Spent some 1:1 time with @thepeninsulatokyo’s Toyota Century on our last day in town today. Magnificent creature.

It truly must be the only Toyota Century in the world that has been painted in Brewster Green. 

Apparently Toyota won’t do a custom color for you because they have this proprietary 8 layer lacquered painting technique, so this particular Century was sold new in Black to The Peninsula before being brought back down to bare metal. It then underwent a commensurate quality repainting in that special green that makes their fleet of Rolls Royces so famous.

All I know is: I must own one someday.

#ToyotaCentury

“Singularly unique, sculptured in design, hand-crafted in Switzerland, and water resistant to three atmospheres. This is *the* sports watch of the ‘80s.
